<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1439,1138,2004]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Medium to large, black and brightly gold colored flies, 
<quantity box="[797,928,1138,1164]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="19.0" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="15.0">15–23 mm</quantity>
. Male tergite 
<number box="[1086,1100,1138,1164]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="6.0">6</number>
with 
<number box="[1167,1181,1138,1164]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
apical short knobs. F. Geller­Grimm notes (pers. comm.) other closely related species with similar structures and shape of terminal segments; a revision of these species is in order. Wings tinged dark yellow. Long mats of bright gold hair on medial and lateral surfaces of tergites. Similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[730,984,1259,1284]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Choerades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amurensis">
<emphasis box="[730,984,1259,1284]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Choerades amurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but much larger, more densely setose flies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1439,1138,2004]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,380,1338,1364]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Redescription.</emphasis>
Head: Face yellow pollinose with yellow gold hair and bristles. Mystax abundant, long, yellow gold. Parafacial hair abundant, yellow gold. Orbital hair yellow, long, erect. Proboscis apically angulated (ventrally angles upwards); apex punctulate (with pits or punctures). Long yellow and black postocular hair. Ocellar tubercle with 
<number box="[477,492,1458,1484]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="6.0">6</number>
exceptionally long yellow bristles. Antenna black with yellow hair and black bristles; relative lengths of segments: 
<number box="[591,606,1498,1524]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[625,636,1498,1524]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[654,671,1498,1524]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
; postpedicel (segment 
<number box="[937,952,1498,1524]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
) with an apical dorsal pit and spine. Thorax: Scutum pale blue black with short, abundant, appressed, yellow acrostichal hair. Postpronotal hair long, yellow. Chaetotaxy with 
<number box="[442,457,1578,1604]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
notopleural, 
<number box="[611,626,1578,1604]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="4.0">4</number>
supraalar, 
<number box="[753,797,1578,1604]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8–9</number>
postalar bristles, all yellow gold. Sparse long fine dorsocentral hair. Discal scutellar hair long, appressed, yellow. Scutellar margin ringed with long yellow bristles. Lateral aspect of thorax black, yellow pollinose. Anepisternum with long sparse yellow and black hair, 
<number box="[1422,1437,1658,1684]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
strong yellow posterior bristles. Katatergal bristles thick, long, yellow. Anatergite bare black integument. Legs: Entirely black with long abundant yellow gold and black hair and bristles. Wings: Tinged yellow, veins darkened. Abdomen: Tergites pale blue black with posterior and lateral mats of short appressed yellow gold hair, longer on apical tergites. Yellow lateral bristles becoming weaker after tergite 
<number box="[1132,1149,1818,1844]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
. Male genitalia: (
<figureCitation box="[1355,1432,1818,1844]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1765,1789]" captionTargetBox="[336,1266,543,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[297,1290,543,1779]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Choerades males — lateral views. 1. C. amurensis. 2. C. caucasicus. 3. C. caudatus. 4. C. japonicus. 5. C. komurai. 6. C. nigrovittatus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175154/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Figs 
<number box="[1415,1432,1818,1844]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.8">2</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,167,1858,1884]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1941,1965]" captionTargetBox="[403,1221,634,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[365,1221,634,1938]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Choerades males — ventral views. 7. C. amurensis. 8. C. caucasicus. 9. C. caudatus. 10. C. japonicus. 11. C. komurai. 12. C. nigrovittatus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175155/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[182,215,1858,1884]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1644,1668]" captionTargetBox="[342,1244,186,1643]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[342,1245,186,1658]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Choerades males — gonopods. 13. C. amurensis. 14. C. caucasicus. 15. C. caudatus. 16. C. japonicus. 17. C. komurai. 18. C. nigrovittatus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175156/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<number box="[182,215,1858,1884]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
.) Dorsal subapical gonocoxite with long filamentous flange with rounded apex. Tergite 
<number box="[1260,1275,1858,1884]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="6.0">6</number>
with 
<number box="[1344,1359,1858,1884]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
apical short knobs, or protuberances, forming a U­shaped apex. Tergite 
<number box="[943,958,1898,1924]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="7.0">7</number>
with a prominent apical knob. Female: Similar to male except apical tergites entirely covered in yellow gold hair. Abdomen clavate, widest on segments 
<number box="[228,243,1978,2004]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="4.0">4</number>
and 
<number box="[300,317,1978,2004]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="5.0">5</number>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
